Food, nutrition and physical activity as the components of human life with an effect on health. Composing an optimal personal diet according to the factors influencing human food requirement. The possibilities of using food, nutrition and physical activity in order to maintain, improve and restore health.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give students a systematic overview of the connections between physical activity, nutrition and health.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) is acquainted with the basic terminology of nutrition and is familiar with digestive processes; 2) is able to analyse the function of different nutrients in the human organism; 3) is able to prepare a balanced menu and analyse a food diary using respective computer programs; 4) is able to analyse connections between nutrition, physical activity and health; 5) is able to analyse the role of nutrition and physical activity in the prevention and treatment of certain illnesses (osteoporosis, diabetes, cardiovascular diseases).
